Datetime conversion
In [15]:
def convert_datetime(df, col):
  df[col] = pd.to_datetime(df[col])
  df['day_of_week'] = df[col].dt.weekday_name 
  df['year'] = df[col].dt.year
  df['month'] = df[col].dt.month 
  df['day'] = df[col].dt.day 
  
  return None

Data cleaning and features creation¶

Latitude, Longitude, Gps_height, Distance¶

Feature Creation attempt: distance¶

We tried to create a distance feature with two different approaches, as you can see in the cell below as comments. However, it actually worsened our score, hence it is commented out in this section.

Imputation of missing coordinates and their corresponding elevation in Train and Test dataset with the help of CARTO and Googlemaps Api¶

  1. Join train and test datasets from website in Dataiku

  2. Upload joined dataset to Carto

  3. Remove outliers with longitude 0 (points in the Atlantic Ocean) from the dataset

Sidenote: only values from the Lake Victoria region and a few select from the Lake Tanganyika region had missing Coordinates

  1. Color each pump based on the basin it gets its water from. In total all pumps have 9 sources of water.
  1. Use “Create Centroids of Geometries” analysis feature and categorize by basin.
    This will give you the center longitude and latitudes for each of the 9 basins (see picture below)

    We replace these with the imputed coordinates in part 6 using Dataiku and a newly downloaded Train and Test dataset.

Date_recorded, time_since, month_record¶

We introduced the time.since in the column. It calculates the time that has passed between 2014-01-01 and the date it was last checked.

total_data["time_since"] = total_data["date_recorded"].apply(
    lambda x: (
        datetime.strptime("2014-01-01", "%Y-%m-%d") -
        datetime.strptime(x, "%Y-%m-%d")

# Please do not run this, as it will take 5 hours. However, you could find the screenshot result below. 
def report(results, n_top=5):
    for i in range(1, n_top + 1):
        candidates = np.flatnonzero(results['rank_test_score'] == i)
        for candidate in candidates:
            print("Model with rank: {0}".format(i))
            print("Mean validation score: {0:.3f} (std: {1:.3f})".format(
                  results['mean_test_score'][candidate],
                  results['std_test_score'][candidate]))
            print("Parameters: {0}".format(results['params'][candidate]))
            print("")
            
report(random_search.cv_results_)
